      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ATTENTION SEEKER (2) was well backed last start but ran below expectations when fourth (20.10), beaten 5 lengths. Was in the money the start prior. Speedy beginner who should be prominent early on from an inside box. Should bounce back. SKETCHY TOBY (1) filled a minor placing last start at this track behind Shaka Goes Bang (20.27) in a Other. Stalked the pace but found the line strongly. Will give a great sight again. URANA JAM DONUT (7) flew the lids from out wide with a slick early split but ran over at the finish when a narrow fourth (23.30) over 400m at Gawler. Has good speed and will be prominent from out wide. Key runner who gets her chance to atone. DEEP PURPLE (5) has a solid strike rate from this box.",
